Recently, when a couple of my family members were ill, I made them this recording of Bible verses to listen to as they healed. They found tremendous comfort in hearing the Word of God and received great peace from these Scriptures during a challenging time. As such, I thought perhaps others could benefit from the recordings as well. 

The entire Bible is edifying and I felt led to these particular verses on healing to strengthen and encourage ones who may need it. 

No matter what a person is going through, good or bad, God is faithful and He walks with us - His Word is true and food for the soul. 

👉🏾This is a short sample, but you can find the full 2 hour version with over 50 Scriptures on healing on my YouTube channel (link is in my profile) . I invite you to check it out for yourself and/or share with another you feel it may serve . ❤️

I pray it blesses you as much as it did my loved ones. God is so very good. Grace and peace to you.

Love, Kimberly 😊
#allglorytoYHWH #teamJesus 🙌🏾

I'm so joyful to share wonderful news with you 😊 
After being introduced by our pastor last winter, a beautiful courtship, falling in love, and lots of prayer, we became engaged. Then, on August 19, 2023, we were blessed to become husband and wife. We made a covenant of holy matrimony before our closest friends, family, and most importantly before God. The Lord has blessed us with each other, and we are so excited to bring Him glory in our life together. It's so amazing because we were both quietly living our individual lives and in obedience to God with no idea that love was around the corner. After we met, we soon knew God's hand of providence brought us to one another.  One never knows the plans YHWH has for our lives, but without a doubt, His are always the best plans! All glory to God! Love, Mr. and Mrs. George E. and Kimberly Elise McCrary 

"For I know the plans I have for you," declares the LORD, "plans to prosper you and not to harm you, plans to give you hope and a future." Jeremiah 29:11 

"But above all these things put on love, which is the bond of perfection. And let the peace of God rule in your hearts, to which also you were called in one body; and be thankful. Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly in all wisdom, teaching and admonishing one another in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing with grace in your hearts to the Lord." Colossians 3:14-16 

"We love because He first loved us" 1 John 4:19

Thank you to all for your kind words, thoughts, and most of all, your prayers for our recent nuptials. We are so very grateful and honored that you have lifted us up with so many positive words and beautiful messages and overall support of God's design and for the institute of marriage. Our first 7 weeks as husband and wife have been truly a blessing, and we look forward to sharing the rest of our lives together ❤️. May we all continue to have faith in God and the hand He has over all of our lives. No matter what things look like in the world,  Jesus is on the throne and  always in control - abide in Him. 🙌🏽. Stay on the narrow path, be set apart, and live for the glory of God.  Love and gratitude. In Christ, George and Kimberly

I've been keeping journals since I was a young girl. Journaling is a wonderful way to recall your life and lessons learned along the way, track goals and growth,  develop creative ideas, pray, and give gratitude to God for the blessings in my life. I love journaling so much that I decided to design my own and what a joy it's been!  Filled with lots of space to write and Bible verses to feed your soul, I love these pretty journals and pray they bless you. To check out the 3 different styles and get more information, click the link in my profile. Have a blessed day! 😇
